-- Pimco Total Return rose 1.25 pct in May -preliminary Morningstar data
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Mon Jun 02, 2014 09:09AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 2 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, the world's largest bond fund run by Bill Gross, rose 1.25 percent in May, beating 79 percent of its peers, preliminary Morningstar data showed on Monday.

The DoubleLine Total Return Bond Fund <DBLTX.O>, a competitor to the Pimco Total Return Fund run by Jeffrey Gundlach, rose 1.13 percent last month, beating 55 percent of its peers, the data showed.